title: Ep 71: Patti Smith, Mapplethorpe & Inventing the Self
description: Remember when people looked like people? I got into Patti Smith on my hiatus from That's Deep Bro and went on a freedom odyssey that lead me to the big, black dongs of Robert Mapplethorpe. What can we learn from big dongs, crooked teeth and the 70's? That maybe you can invent who are you are and stop worrying so much about conforming. Freedom!
author: nadav@ymhstudios.com (Christina Pazsitzky)
